Change-Id: I4872d34578ea0861463e70fd3c30da31216a0a7b","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TheRakeshPurohit/tensorflow/commits/f2b6e222ed8d3dd906d53b06aca1c570fd771ceb"},{"sha":"dcb95ca4a6efd9534f72047ffbc3f9c8cbd1fca9","author":{"email":"7da1985d121fd79537822bb42be62798d2d2aa23@google.com","name":"Prakalp Srivastava"},"message":"Add optional attributes to specify operand/result layouts in mhlo::CustomCallOp.

A custom call can also have layout constrains on operands and results which can be specified as optional `operand_layouts` and `result_layouts` attributes. The layout attribute is an array of rank-1 index tensors and the i-th layout attribute specifies the layout for i-th operand/result.

The `operand_layouts` & `result_layouts` attributes can be specified under the following constraints checked in the verifier:
1) Either both `operand_layouts` and `result_layouts` are specified or none.
2) None of the operands are of tuple type.
3) None of the results are of tuple type except the common case of single tuple result packing non-tuple values is allowed. In this case the i-th `result_layouts` attribute specifies the layout of i-th element in the result tuple.

[{"sha":"a24f714bc95d20162297a019b6477bf1350db765","author":{"email":"a1bdfbfb01322b54f9edf8cea8f328c9384b211a@degeneration.co.uk","name":"Martin Atkins"},"message":"command/init: Skip redundant state migration prompt in Cloud mode

The specialized Terraform Cloud migration process asks right up top
whether the user wants to migrate state, because there are various other
questions contingent on that answer.

Therefore we ought to just honor their earlier answer when we get to the
point of actually doing the state migration, rather than prompting again.

This is tricky because we're otherwise just reusing a codepath that's
common to both modes. Hopefully we can find a better way to do this in
a later commit, but for the moment our main motivation is minimizing risk
to the very next release.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/a24f714bc95d20162297a019b6477bf1350db765"}]

[{"sha":"a24f714bc95d20162297a019b6477bf1350db765","author":{"email":"a1bdfbfb01322b54f9edf8cea8f328c9384b211a@degeneration.co.uk","name":"Martin Atkins"},"message":"command/init: Skip redundant state migration prompt in Cloud mode

The specialized Terraform Cloud migration process asks right up top
whether the user wants to migrate state, because there are various other
questions contingent on that answer.

Therefore we ought to just honor their earlier answer when we get to the
point of actually doing the state migration, rather than prompting again.

This is tricky because we're otherwise just reusing a codepath that's
common to both modes. Hopefully we can find a better way to do this in
a later commit, but for the moment our main motivation is minimizing risk
to the very next release.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/a24f714bc95d20162297a019b6477bf1350db765"},{"sha":"e3f4f2ba1b3e2434dec83e5759a450d7450dbdf6","author":{"email":"2a56ea1490dced68c01a1ee616138a226895907a@users.noreply.github.com","name":"The Terraform Team"},"message":"Merge a24f714bc95d20162297a019b6477bf1350db765 into backport/f-cloud-integration-migrations/separately-renewing-mole","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/e3f4f2ba1b3e2434dec83e5759a450d7450dbdf6"}]

cty: The documented definition and comparison logic of cty.Number is now
refined to acknowledge that its true range is limited only to values
that have both a binary floating point and decimal representation,
because cty values are primarily designed to traverse JSON serialization
where numbers are always defined as decimal strings.

In particular, that means that two cty.Number values now always compare
as equal if their representation in JSON (under cty's own JSON encoder)
would be equal, even though the decimal approximation we use for that
conversion is slightly lossy. This pragmatic compromise avoids confusing
situations where a round-trip through JSON serialization (or other
serializations that use the same number format) may produce a value that
doesn't compare equal to the original.

This new definition of equals should not cause any significant behavior
change for any integer in our in-memory storage range, but may cause
some fractional values to compare equal where they didn't before if they
differ only by a small fraction.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/ca6d3cf50f5cf92f168069fa17846d6b5d0622ea"},{"sha":"858dc96859aeb1975703e8a2e290e2da807833c4","author":{"email":"711c73f64afdce07b7e38039a96d2224209e9a6c@chrisarcand.com","name":"Chris Arcand"},"message":"Merge pull request #29853 from hashicorp/cloud-tags-workspace

Fix typo in 0.13 upgrade guide","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/19101df1d4d04cab44d169b0177817ea711dc39b"},{"sha":"5ac1074c541f6e2dff4e05459764cf9f943168d3","author":{"email":"a1bdfbfb01322b54f9edf8cea8f328c9384b211a@degeneration.co.uk","name":"Martin Atkins"},"message":"main: Report version information for "interesting" dependencies

We have a few dependencies that are such a significant part of Terraform's
behavior that they will often be the root cause of or the solution to a
bug reported against Terraform.

As a small quality-of-life improvement to help with diagnosing those,
we'll now report the selected versions for each of these so-called
"interesting" dependencies as part of our initial trace log output during
Terraform startup.

The goal here is that when someone opens a bug report, and includes the
trace log as our bug report template requests, we'll be able to see at a
glance which versions of these dependencies were involved, instead of
having to manually cross-reference in the go.mod file of the reported main
Terraform CLI version.

This does slightly grow the general overhead of the logs, but as long as
we keep this set of interesting dependencies relatively small it shouldn't
present any significant problem in typical usage.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/5ac1074c541f6e2dff4e05459764cf9f943168d3"}]

Fix typo in 0.13 upgrade guide","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/19101df1d4d04cab44d169b0177817ea711dc39b"},{"sha":"5ac1074c541f6e2dff4e05459764cf9f943168d3","author":{"email":"a1bdfbfb01322b54f9edf8cea8f328c9384b211a@degeneration.co.uk","name":"Martin Atkins"},"message":"main: Report version information for "interesting" dependencies

We have a few dependencies that are such a significant part of Terraform's
behavior that they will often be the root cause of or the solution to a
bug reported against Terraform.

As a small quality-of-life improvement to help with diagnosing those,
we'll now report the selected versions for each of these so-called
"interesting" dependencies as part of our initial trace log output during
Terraform startup.

The goal here is that when someone opens a bug report, and includes the
trace log as our bug report template requests, we'll be able to see at a
glance which versions of these dependencies were involved, instead of
having to manually cross-reference in the go.mod file of the reported main
Terraform CLI version.

This does slightly grow the general overhead of the logs, but as long as
we keep this set of interesting dependencies relatively small it shouldn't
present any significant problem in typical usage.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/5ac1074c541f6e2dff4e05459764cf9f943168d3"}]

cty: The documented definition and comparison logic of cty.Number is now
refined to acknowledge that its true range is limited only to values
that have both a binary floating point and decimal representation,
because cty values are primarily designed to traverse JSON serialization
where numbers are always defined as decimal strings.

In particular, that means that two cty.Number values now always compare
as equal if their representation in JSON (under cty's own JSON encoder)
would be equal, even though the decimal approximation we use for that
conversion is slightly lossy. This pragmatic compromise avoids confusing
situations where a round-trip through JSON serialization (or other
serializations that use the same number format) may produce a value that
doesn't compare equal to the original.

This new definition of equals should not cause any significant behavior
change for any integer in our in-memory storage range, but may cause
some fractional values to compare equal where they didn't before if they
differ only by a small fraction.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/ca6d3cf50f5cf92f168069fa17846d6b5d0622ea"},{"sha":"858dc96859aeb1975703e8a2e290e2da807833c4","author":{"email":"711c73f64afdce07b7e38039a96d2224209e9a6c@chrisarcand.com","name":"Chris Arcand"},"message":"Merge pull request #29853 from hashicorp/cloud-tags-workspace

[{"sha":"aef782f34844e70c79481cbecd35b01c9bb25ffa","author":{"email":"64b2b6d12bfe4baae7dad3d018f8cbf6b0e7a044@gone.nl","name":"Sebastiaan van Stijn"},"message":"update containerd binary to v1.5.8

The eighth patch release for containerd 1.5 contains a mitigation for CVE-2021-41190
as well as several fixes and updates.

Notable Updates

* Handle ambiguous OCI manifest parsing
* Filter selinux xattr for image volumes in CRI plugin
* Use DeactiveLayer to unlock layers that cannot be renamed in Windows snapshotter
* Fix pull failure on unexpected EOF
* Close task IO before waiting on delete
* Log a warning for ignored invalid image labels rather than erroring

[{"sha":"8e49436cf657886d0094939a27eff0ce04f10229","author":{"email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org","name":"A. Unique TensorFlower"},"message":"Move responsibility for avoiding version-specific bugs to stream_executor.

Fused conv ops and XLA had competing versions of this logic that didn't agree,
and it was causing some confusion.  Now the knowledge of what bugs exist at
particular cuDNN versions lives entirely in stream_executor, and callers just
specify whether cuDNN frontend should be preferred when it works.

This also results in enabling cuDNN frontend for identity-activation fused
convs in XLA, which were previously disabled.

[{"sha":"4e74f5c6ce9936739c9e9f0536c58bac78f15f15","author":{"email":"4733e76aa05f451fa375889c85b599266aa9962f@google.com","name":"Bixia Zheng"},"message":"PR #52671: [TF-TRT] Adding a detailled unconversion report capability on demand

Imported from GitHub PR https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/52671

@bixia1 @tfeher for review

This PR does the following:
- Adds `TF_TRT_SHOW_DETAILED_REPORT=1` capability to modify the conversion
report and increase verbosity.
- Changes `struct ConversionParams.output_names` to `struct
ConversionParams.input_output_names` to be more precise on the actual use of
the parameter.
- Removes `at <layer_name>` from the error message generated for unconverted
ops
  - allows similar errors generated at different layers to be grouped together
  - removes some redundancy where the information is "double printed"

The eighth patch release for containerd 1.5 contains a mitigation for CVE-2021-41190
as well as several fixes and updates.

Notable Updates

* Handle ambiguous OCI manifest parsing
* Filter selinux xattr for image volumes in CRI plugin
* Use DeactiveLayer to unlock layers that cannot be renamed in Windows snapshotter
* Fix pull failure on unexpected EOF
* Close task IO before waiting on delete
* Log a warning for ignored invalid image labels rather than erroring
* Update pull to handle of non-https urls in descriptors

See the changelog for complete list of changes
